<H3> <TI>   Poland's Walesa Begins Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poland's Walesa Begins Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1805100794 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 0832 GMT 18 
May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1805100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Poland/Italy: President Walesa in </F>
Rome"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 18 -- Polish President Lech Walesa 
arrived in Rome today with a large delegation of Warsaw 
government representatives to a welcome led by Polish Premier 
Waldemar Pawlak, who came to this capital yesterday. 
  Following Walesa's arrival, aboard a Polish Air Force flight 
which landed at the Ciampino military and civilian airport, the 
full delegation departed for Cassino, midway between Rome and 
Naples, for a ceremony marking the 50th anniversary of the World 
War II battle of Montecassino. 
  In fierce fighting during the offensive mounted against a 
German stronghold by Allied troops, including the II Polish Army 
Corps, more than 2,000 Polish soldiers were killed. Cassino is 
also the site of Italy's largest Polish cemetery. 
  This evening, the visiting president will return to Rome for 
a meeting with Head of State Oscar Luigi Scalfaro. Tomorrow, 
Walesa will go to Rome's Catholic Gemelli Hospital for a visit 
to his friend and compatriot, Pope John Paul II, who is 
recovering from surgery following a broken leg. The president 
will return to Warsaw tomorrow in the early afternoon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

