<H3> <TI>   Agnelli Favors Government's Economic Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agnelli Favors Government's Economic Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1805102094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1432 GMT 17 
May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1805102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Agnelli on Government Program, </F>
Confidence Vote"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 17 -- Fiat chairman and 
Senator-for-Life Gianni Agnelli today voiced a favorable opinion 
of the government's economic program and expressed his hope that 
the executive of Premier Silvio Berlusconi wins Wednesday's [18 
May] confidence vote in the Senate. 
  Speaking to the press following a luncheon of life senators, 
offered by Senate Speaker Carlo Scognamiglio, the Fiat chairman 
explained how the government economic program aimed at 
stimulating economic growth while, at the same time, limiting 
risks. The positive aspects of the program, outlined by 
Berlusconi to the Senate yesterday, included, Agnelli said: the 
commitment to curb public spending; boosting the economy through 
investments and greater flexibility on labor costs. 
  Turning his attention to tomorrow's confidence vote in the 
Senate, Agnelli said "I hope the government makes it" in reply 
to those who asked how he would vote. 
  Asked to comment on the positions of the other life 
Senators, 
the Fiat chairman said "I believe that each senator maintains 
his own opinion. On the other hand, life senators are 
individuals and each decides for himself". 
  The other life senators attending the luncheon were 
ex-president Francesco Cossiga, former Senate Speaker Giovanni 
Spadolini, Giulio Andreotti, Francesco De Martino and Paolo 
Emilio Taviani. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

