<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn/Ankara (DPA) -- According to eyewitness 
reports, Turkish and Iranian troops have intervened in the 
internal Kurdish conflict in northeastern Iraq. In the 
Sulaimaniya area, thousands are fleeing from the fighting, 
Eberhard Walde, chief of the German Liaison Bureau in the 
region, told DPA in Bonn in a telephone interview on 19 May. 
  He said that while Iranian artillery attacked Kurdish 
settlements from the east, Turkish aircraft dropped bombs from 
the north, which has led to another stream of civilian refugees. 
Meanwhile, the autonomous Kurdish region in Iraq has virtually 
been shared between the two rival parties, the Patriotic Union 
of Kurdistan and the Democratic Party of Kurdistan, which are 
continuing their armed conflicts, Walde said. [passage omitted] 

