<F P=100> BENELUX COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> The Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Refuses Troops for Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Refuses Troops for Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005181394 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1730 GMT 
20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Dutch Cabinet has announced that the security 
situation in Rwanda is so bad that, for the time being, the 
Netherlands is not to provide troops for a UN peacekeeping 
force. Apparently, the gruesome murder of 10 Belgian blue 
helmets in Rwanda last month was an important factor in the 
Dutch Cabinet's decision. Rwanda used to be a Belgian colony 
and the Dutch ministers fear that Dutch soldiers could be 
mistaken for Belgians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

