<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dasa, Aerospatiale Plan Joint Holding Society </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dasa, Aerospatiale Plan Joint Holding Society </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005163894 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
20 May 94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ottobrunn near Munich -- The aviation and aerospace 
company of Daimler-Benz and the French aviation concern 
Aerospatiale have now specified their plans for a joint venture 
in the production of satellites. As Aerospatiale boss Louis 
Gallois reportedly announced in Cannes (southern France), a 
holding society is to be founded in Munich before the end of the 
year in which the two enterprises are to participate on a 50:50 
percent basis. Negotiations on this cooperation have not yet 
been concluded, a spokesman of the German Aerospace AG company 
stressed. According to Gallois, the two firms hope to achieve 
results by July. The partners believe that, in a self-confident 
manner, they will jointly become the largest European producer 
of satellites and a serious competitor for the English-French 
Matra-Marconi group. 

</TEXT>

