  [Text] Paris, May 21, IRNA -- Iran and France reached an 
agreement on rescheduling of Iranian debts here Friday [20 May]. 
  An Iranian Embassy spokesman in an interview with IRNA here 
said the financial accord was reached after two days of 
negotiation between representatives of the Iranian Central Bank 
and the French Economic Ministry. 
  The spokesman also said the two sides could solve the main 
points of the financial accord within a broad framework while 
the remaining details would be worked out in the near future. 

