<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Will Not Discuss Changes in UN Document </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis Will Not Discuss Changes in UN Document </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005211794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2005211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis has said explicitly that 
he will not agree to discuss any changes to the 21 March UN 
document on the confidence-building measures. He said: I have 
accepted this document. Either Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf 
Denktas accepts it too, or we don't play anymore. Kliridhis 
clarified that he has not been informed that the United Nations 
has accepted any changes to the UN document, as reported by the 
Turkish Cypriot press. 
  The president was speaking this afternoon after meeting AKEL 
[Restorative Party of the Working People] Secretary General 
Dhimitrios Khristofias, in his series of meetings to brief the 
political leaders before the National Council convenes. 
Kliridhis said if measures are taken to make the Turkish side 
show willingness for a solution, then the substance of the 
Cyprus issue will be discussed. 
  Khristofias said he and Kliridhis agreed that after the 
failure of the talks on the confidence-building measures the 
process must return to the substance of the Cyprus issue, but on 
the condition that Denktas and Ankara are forced to abandon 
their intransigent stance. He added that the UN Security 
Council must make decisions about drastic measures to bend 
Turkish intransigence, but expressed reservations about this 
possibility. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

