to accept the confidence-building measures, which he described 
as important. The British official also referred to the British 
Government's continuing interest in reaching an agreement on the 
confidence-building measures. But added, he is not in a 
position to know whether Denktas is willing to change his stance 
to facilitate moves toward an agreement. [passage omitted] 

