<H3> <TI>   British Foreign Office Official Arrives 23 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    British Foreign Office Official Arrives 23 May </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Comments on Purpose of Visit </H4>

<F P=102> NC2205184294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2205184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] British Deputy Foreign Secretary Tom Richardson 
arrived in Cyprus this afternoon. [passage omitted] 
  Richardson said his country wants to see the 
confidence-building measures succeed and described them as a 
very significant step. He added that he does not believe the 
confidence-building measures process has failed. 
  Asked if the reason for his visit is to persuade Turkish 
Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas to accept the confidence-building 
measures, the British official said his country has been 
attempting this for a long time. He added: The British 
Government is in continuous contact with Turkish Prime Minister 
Tansu Ciller, Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, and the 
leaders of the Turkish Cypriot community. Richardson said he 
assumed his current duties three months ago, but that he had 
dealt with the Cyprus issue in his former position of British 
alternate representative to the United Nations. 

