<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   PKK Denies Casualties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PKK Denies Casualties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005192494 Istanbul OZGUR ULKE in Turkish 19 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul OZGUR ULKE </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Several Turkish military aircraft bombed the Zalakh 
camp in northern Iraq at about 1200 yesterday. We contacted the 
Kurdish Workers Party's Kurdish People's Liberation Army [KPLA] 
Press Office immediately after the hour-long air attack. The 
KPLA Press Office confirmed the air attack, and said there were 
no casualties in the camp. 
  However, the Turkish General Staff Press and Public 
Relations 
Office stated that the air operation took place from 1200 to 
1220. It said that 19 aircraft took part in the attack on Zalakh 
camp and that the aircraft returned to their bases after 
destroying their targets. 
  The Zalakh camp was bombed for the first time on 28 January, 
after the government's move to devalue the Turkish lira. A 
statement made at the time said all of the targets were 
destroyed. 

</TEXT>

