<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister To Visit Baghdad in June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister To Visit Baghdad in June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2005181894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Mehmet Gulcegun, deputy leader of the Social 
Democratic Populist Party [SDPP], has said that the Habur border 
gate with Iraq will regain its old vitality in the coming period. 
  At a news conference in Ankara, Gulcegun said this step will 
partly alleviate the load placed on the Turkish economy by the 
embargo imposed on Iraq. Furthermore, he said, reopening the 
Habur border gate will end the crisis in the transportation 
sector, which is an important source of income in southeast 
Anatolia. 
  Gulcegun pointed out that Murat Karayalcin, SDPP leader and 
deputy prime minister, will go to Baghdad next month. During 
the visit, the SDPP deputy leader said, work will be conducted 
to develop cooperation possibilities. 
  [Begin Gulcegun recording] We are trying to solve the Habur 
problem, because it is the source of other negative developments 
in the region. Loyal to the unity of the country and to the 
state, the industrious regional people will make use of this 
opportunity in the best possible way. They will ensure their 
income while contributing to the economy of our country. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

