<H3> <TI>   Ahtisaari Comments on Vayrynen Anti-EU Stand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ahtisaari Comments on Vayrynen Anti-EU Stand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94EN0325B Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 27 Apr 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> 94EN0325B </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Ahtisaari Questions Vayrynen's Views </F>
on the EU"] 
  [Text] President Martti Ahtisaari commented on former 
Foreign Minister Paavo Vayrynen's (Center Party) suggestion, 
according to which Finland's membership in the European Union 
[EU] should be postponed. Ahtisaari noted, in connection with an 
article that appeared in the newspaper SAVON SANOMAT last 
Tuesday [26 April], that such a debate should have taken place 
at the time when Vayrynen was also in the cabinet and was party 
to the decision to apply for membership. 
  Ahtisaari said that he had not noticed Vayrynen's comments 
receiving any significant support from within the party. 
  "This is the opinion of a single citizen, who, of course, is 
entitled to voice it," concluded Ahtisaari. 

</TEXT>

