<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas' Acceptance Uncertain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas' Acceptance Uncertain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2105151494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1400 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2105151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There is no information that Turkish Cypriot leader 
Rauf Denktas has accepted the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] and there is no reason for the UN secretary general to 
delay his report to the Security Council. The report is 
expected to be submitted next week. 
  In a telephone conversation this morning, Gustave Feissel, 
the UN secretary general's alternate special representative in 
Cyprus, reiterated this statement to President Glavkos 
Kliridhis. Government Spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the 
president contacted Feissel to find out if the UN secretary 
general would delay his report. He added that Kliridhis made it 
clear to Feissel that he has accepted the 21 March UN document 
as is and that he will not accept any changes either in the form 
of interpretations or clarifications. President Kliridhis 
stressed that the 21 March document is crystal clear in its 
contents. 

</TEXT>

