<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials React To Herzog Victory, Speech </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials React To Herzog Victory, Speech </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kohl Calls SPD `Bad Loser' </H4>

<F P=102> LD2405114894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1018 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl described 
the great unity with which the CDU/CSU [Christian Democrat 
Union/Christian Socialist Union] group voted for Roman Herzog in 
the presidential elections yesterday as very important. He was 
also very pleased that the majority of representatives of the 
FDP [Free Democratic Party] had also voted for Herzog, Kohl said 
in Berlin today. The chancellor leveled harsh criticism at the 
Social Democrats. He said he could not understand the 
complaints of several SPD representatives. The SPD has proved 
itself a bad loser. 

</TEXT>

