  [Text] Arber Xhaferri, chairman of the Party for 
Democratic Prosperity [PDP], has arrived for a one-week visit in 
Copenhagen to hold meetings at the Danish Foreign Ministry with 
representatives from CSCE and the Danish Social Democratic Party. 
  During a meeting today with the leadership of the PDP branch 
in Denmark, Mr. Arber Xhaferri presented the current situation 
in The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM] and the 
activities of this party, the largest of the Albanians in this 
Republic, about the extraordinary census and future 
parliamentary elections. 

