<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Autonomy Party in New Caledonia Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Autonomy Party in New Caledonia Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2005105694 Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS in French 20 May 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BR2005105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Philippe Pentecost, a businessman of European 
origin, and Nidoish Naisseline, the Kanak separatist leader, 
yesterday established a new Caledonian political party that 
advocates the establishment of an "autonomous Caledonian state, 
a member of the Francophone community and the EC." The party is 
called "1999," which is the year following the referendum on 
self-determination provided for in the 1988 Matignon accords. 

</TEXT>

