<F P=103> AU2105185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Dortmund -- Rudolf Scharping, chairman of the 
Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD], has called for more 
European Union funds for Germany. During his party's European 
festival in Dortmund, the candidate for the chancellor's office 
stated today that, in view of the economic situation, Germany is 
paying too much for the European Union. "We have fallen back to 
seventh place in the European prosperity scale. For this 
reason, the return of European funds to Germany must increase," 
Scharping stressed on the sidelines of the SPD rally on the 
occasion of the European elections, which was attended by 
approximately 300,000 people, according to the police. 
  During his speech, Scharping advocated a stronger role of 
the 
European Parliament and rejected a "European central state with 
excessive bureaucracy." The identity of the regions must be 
preserved. With a view to European financial policies, the SPD 
chairman pointed out that he prefers a stable German mark to an 
unstable European currency that is introduced too early. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

