<H4>    Discusses Bosnia, Arms Embargo </H4>

<F P=102> AU2005194394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov stated 
in Ankara that Bulgaria does not oppose the participation of 
Turkish troops in the UN peacekeeping forces in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Ending two days of talks with his host, 
Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, Daskalov stressed that 
regional countries in principle should not send their troops on 
such delicate missions. 
  Cetin and Daskalov expressed the concern of their 
governments 
over the continuation of the war in Bosnia, and called on the 
international community to put in an added effort in order to 
end the Bosnia-Herzegovina drama. The two sides also expressed 
their commitment to ending the embargo against 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. According to domestic media reports, 
Ministers Cetin and Daskalov said this should be done as soon as 
possible. 

