<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fourteen `Terrorists' Captured in Istanbul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fourteen `Terrorists' Captured in Istanbul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2305145694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1435 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2305145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, May 23 (A.A) -- Fourteen terrorists 
including two women were captured during operations by security 
forces in Istanbul, it was reported on Monday [23 May]. 
  A statement by security headquarters said among those 
captured were also military leaders of the terrorist 
organization. 
  Automatic rifles, handguns, hand grenades and material used 
in making bombs were also seized in searches of their houses and 
hide outs. 
  The statement said that the operations were started on May 
10, adding that those captured were responsible for activities 
such as the killing of one police officer, the bombing of two 
coffee houses, a furniture shop, an official building in 
different districts of the city. 
  It was also determined they had taken part in the bombing of 
an election office and two private offices. 
  One of the terrorists is a military leader of the terrorist 
PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization and was trained in 
Greece, following which he came to Turkey, the statement also 
said. 
  Another terrorist, a woman, was a secretary at the office of 
the now-banned, pro-Kurdish DEP [Democratic] Party, it was 
reported. 
  Police said the investigation continues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

