<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Predicts `Pro-Israeli' Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Predicts `Pro-Israeli' Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405185294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1758 GMT 
24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "This Italian government will be the most 
pro-Israeli in the past 20 years". These were the words with 
which Foreign Minister Antonio Martino who is currently visiting 
Washington, sought to reassure the Jewish-American community. 
  At the next G-7 meeting Martino will ask for condemnation of 
"the ongoing Arab economic boycott of Israel." 
  Martino met earlier with U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher, who said "he has a lot of faith in the government 
that resulted from the elections: we are ready to work together." 

</TEXT>

