<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has stated that the 
Turkish people give special importance to furthering 
Turkish-German relations. Demirel sent a congratulatory message 
to Roman Herzog on his election as Germany's president. 
  According to a statement issued by the Press Center of the 
President's Office, Demirel wished Herzog success in his new 
appointment. The statement further notes: The Turkish nation 
attaches special importance to furthering relations with Germany 
because of the deep-rooted historical ties between the two 
countries and the 2 million Turkish citizens living in Germany. 
Expressing his belief that the traditional Turkish-German 
cooperation and friendliness will be furthered during Herzog's 
term, Demirel added that he is always ready and willing to 
cooperate on this issue. 

</TEXT>

