<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosions Injure 2 at Istanbul Train Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosions Injure 2 at Istanbul Train Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2505053094 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2505053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two people have been slightly injured after four 
[number as heard] concussion grenades [ses bombasi], set with a 
timing mechanism, exploded in Istanbul's Harem Station. The 
grenades, planted at the train station by unidentified persons, 
went off at short intervals beginning at approximately 2300 last 
night. 
  Sevki Mustafaoglu was injured in the leg and taken to 
Haydarpasa Hospital, and Murat Yaman was treated on the scene. 
  Officials stated that one of the concussion grenades was 
placed inside a telephone booth, one at a coffee shop, and 
another at the back entrance to a police station in the train 
station. An investigation is under way. 
  Meanwhile, at around the same time, a Molotov cocktail was 
thrown at Sisli's Bag-Kur [Social Security Association for 
Tradesmen, Artisans, and Independent Workers] building. No one 
was injured in the incident. 

</TEXT>

