<H3> <TI>   Europe Stability Conference Opens in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Europe Stability Conference Opens in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605085494 Paris AFP in English 0817 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2605085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, May 26 (AFP) -- A two-day conference of 57 
countries opened here Thursday [26 May] with the aim of defusing 
possible new wars in Europe by settling potential border 
disputes and solving the problems of minorities. 
  The conference, opened by UNESCO director general Federico 
Mayor at the organisation's headquarters here, is the brainchild 
of French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur. 
  It will aim to frame a Stability Pact which would be signed 
by the end of the year for potential new candidates to the 
European Union (EU). 
  Russia is respresented at the conference by Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and the United States by Undersecretary of State 
for Political Affairs Peter Tarnoff. 
  French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe has said the summit aims 
to settle border and minority problems between "countries with 
the vocation of entering the EU," following the collapse of the 
Soviet bloc. 

</TEXT>

