<H3> <TI>   Ruling Coalition Gains Chamber Chairmanships </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruling Coalition Gains Chamber Chairmanships </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505183294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1548 GMT 
25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ruling coalition has gained the chairmanships 
of the Chamber of Deputies committees. The outcome of the 
voting was a foregone conclusion, except for the the foreign 
affairs committee, where Mirko Tremaglia from the National 
Alliance won over Emma Bonino from the Radical Party by a single 
vote. 
  Following is the full list of chairmen of the parliamentary 
committees: 
  Gustavo Selva (constitutional affairs) and Paolo 
Agostinacchio (finance) from the National Alliance; 
  Paolo Bampo (defense), Roberto Calderoli (social affairs), 
Marco Sartori (labor), Alberto Paolo Lembo (agriculture), and 
Francesco Formenti (environment) from the Northern League; 
  Tiziana Maiolo (justice), Silvio Liotta (budget), Vittorio 
Sgarbi (culture), and Alessandro Rubino from Forza Italia; 
  and Sante Perticaro (transport) from the Christian Democrat 
Center. 

</TEXT>

